description.narrative: The Project Development Objective is to strengthen agricultural production systems and facilitate access to market for targeted value chains among small and medium scale commercial farmers in the five participating states. These value chains are rice, oil palm, cocoa, fruit trees, poultry production, aquaculture and dairy, with maize and rice as staples.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Schedule II, Section II (a)(1) | Description :The recipient shall monitor and evaluate the project's progressand prepare project reports to cover one calendar quarter. Report shall be furnished to IDA not later than 30 after the reportperiod. | Due Date :30-Sep-2009

Finance Agreement :Schedule II, Section II (b)(1) | Description :The recipient shall maintain a financial system in accordance withprovision of section 4.09 of general conditions. | Due Date :30-Jun-2009

Finance Agreement :Schedule II, Section II (b)(2) | Description :The recipient shall prepare and furnish to IDA, not later than 30days after the end of calendar semester, interim unaudited financial reports for the project covering the semester. | Frequency:Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule II, Section II (b)(3) | Description :The recipient shall have its financial statements of the projectaudited which covers period of one fiscal year and furnished to IDA not later than six months after the period. | Frequency :Yearly
